description:
This issue features some sneak peeks of the upcoming Series 7B stories plus Steven Moffat reveals what trouble lies ahead for the Doctor and Clara in The Bells of St John.

It’s the traditional Doctor Who thing of taking something omnipresent in your life and making it sinister, if something did get in the Wi-Fi, we’d be kind of screwed. Nobody had really done it before, so I thought, ‘It’s time to get kids frightened of Wi-Fi!

Also in this issue:

He was the Doctor! – In the second part of DWM’s previously unpublished interview with Jon Pertwee, conducted a year before his death in 1996, the actor who played the Third Doctor reveals his thoughts on his departure from Doctor Who, the untimely death of Master actor Roger Delgado, and his relationship with the show and its fans in later years.

Craig A Tur! – Frazer Hines recalls his adventures in time and space in the 60s series as kilt-wearing companion to the Second Doctor, Jamie McCrimmon – and why he wants to come back…

Completely Pointless! – DWM goes behind the scenes on the forthcoming Doctor Who edition of the BBC quiz show, Pointless Celebrities and talks to contestants Sylvester McCoy, Louise Jameson, Nicola Bryant, Bernard Cribbins, Frazer Hines, Sophie Aldred, John Leeson and Andrew Hayden-Smith!

Setting Sail In Space… – There’s trouble aboard ship as the Fifth Doctor, Tegan and Turlough take part in a race through space, and encounter a race of Eternals! Discover a wealth of fascinating facts about the last story in 1983's 'Black Guardian trilogy' as Enlightenment is put under the spotlight in The Fact of Fiction.

The Man Who Knows… - The big boss answers some of your most pressing Doctor Who questions in this issue’s Ask Steven Moffat – including one from one of his predecessors…

The Good, The Bard, and The Ugly… – Hey nonny nonny! The Tenth Doctor and Martha Jones go back to Elizabethan England and meet the most famous writer in history, as The Time Team watch The Shakespeare Code.

Masters Of The Hunt! – The Doctor is reunited with his old friends, Ian and Barbara, while flaming-skulled warriors cause havoc on the world of Cornucopia? The action heats up in Part Three of our epic comic-strip adventure Hunters of the Burning Stone, written by Scott Gray and illustrated by Martin Geraghty.

The Trip Of A Lifetime! – DWM turns back the clock to 2005 when Doctor Who made its momentous return to our TV screens, with Christopher Eccleston as the Doctor and Billie Piper as his companion, Rose Tyler. The voyage through five decades of Doctor Who with the twenty-seventh series of the show in Countdown to 50!

DVD Dilemmas! – Jacqueline Rayner shares the ups and downs of a family in love with Doctor Who and tackles the controversial topic of how to order your DVDs on your shelf, in this issue’s Relative Dimensions.

A Burning Question - Wotcha! ponders just which planets in the Doctor Who universe have seas of acid in The History of Doctor Who in 100 Objects, challenges you to spot the false fact in a Shakesperian-themed Six Faces of Delusion, and consults The Stockbridge English Dictionary for some more unusual definitions.

PLUS! All the latest official news, TV and merchandise reviews, previews, a prize-winning competitions and crossword and much, much more!

description:
Have we got a treat for you! Starting in this issue of DC UNIVERSE PRESENTS, we’re bringing you the adventures of a different kind of super hero team: JUSTICE LEAGUE DARK! Led by everyone’s favourite occult detective, John Constantine, this ragtag crew of mystical misfits are here to handle the tasks too paranormal for the likes of Superman et al!

We’ve also got two new stories featuring the original Justice League. Discover what happens when a new member tries to join the team, and don’t miss the prologue to the next big arc, THE VILLAIN’S JOURNEY!

Inside the latest issue:

JUSTICE LEAGUE – The Villain’s Journey: Prologue

Five years on from witnessing the origin of the Justice League we catch up with Earth’s finest team of super heroes as a new threat appears on the horizon! Plus, don’t miss the reintroduction of the team’s greatest champion, Steve Trevor!

First printed in Justice League #7

JUSTICE LEAGUE – Team Up: Green Arrow

The Justice League rarely opens their ranks to new members – but why? As the Emerald Archer, Green Arrow, tries to join the team, there’s one hero who’s dead against his candidacy: Aquaman!

First printed in Justice League #8

JUSTICE LEAGUE DARK – The Black Room: Part 1

Brand new strip! John Constantine leads a team of supernatural heroes – including Zatanna, Deadman and Black Orchid – to steal a map to the source of all magic out of the clutches of the nefarious Felix Faust! Don’t miss the beginning of the story that will rock the landscape of the DC universe!

First printed in Justice League Dark #9

There’s a new villain in town in our brand new arc of JUSTICE LEAGUE – and he’s not a guy you’d want to mess with! Over in JUSTICE LEAGUE DARK, the magic continues with Constantine and his cohorts, as all is not what it seems in the House of Mystery!

Inside the latest issue:

JUSTICE LEAGUE – The Villain’s Journey: The Call for Adventure

It’s the start of our fantastic new Justice League arc ‘The Villain’s Journey’! An all-new major nemesis takes his first steps to tear apart Earth’s mightiest heroes! His first target: Steve Trevor.

First printed in Justice League #9

JUSTICE LEAGUE – The Villain’s Journey: The Belly of the Beast

The latest villain to target the Justice League reveals himself to the team! But can the League pull themselves together in time to defeat a foe that knows everything about them?

First printed in Justice League #10

JUSTICE LEAGUE DARK – The Black Room: Part Two

It’s the second part of our brand new strip! After gaining possession of the map to the Books of Magic, John Constantine and his team travel to the House of Mystery to work out their next move. But with Constantine in charge, things don’t exactly go according to plan…

First printed in Justice League Dark #10

Hocus pocus! Abracadabra! Open Sesame! All famous words that we’ve been uttering since childhood in the vain hope that something magical would happen. But what if magic was real? And what if a single word could turn you into a superhero? Well wonder no longer, DUCP fans, as we present a brand new story that will effect the future of the Justice League! Get ready for SHAZAM!

Inside the latest issue:

Justice League: The Villain’s Journey – Atonement

New villain on the block, Rupert Graves has been interrogating liaison to the Justice League, Steve Trevor, to learn everything he can about Earth’s greatest team of superheroes. Having infiltrated the Justice League Watchtower, Graves left the league teetering on the edge of madness, dealing with their inner demons. Are the heroes able to pull themselves together to defeat this new threat?

First printed in Justice League #11

Shazam!: The Curse of Shazam! – Part One

The start of an all-new story that ties directly into the Justice League later this year! Billy Baston is one trouble-making teenager, but his whole life is about to change thanks to one magic word!

First printed in Justice League #7 and #8

Justice League Dark: The Black Room – Part Three

The race to locate the Books of Magic continues! Constantine has inadvertently unleashed the Demons Three upon the ARGUS facility – can Steve Trevor and the team stop the Demons from freeing Felix Faust? Plus! A traitor is revealed!

First printed in Justice League Dark #11
